The ancient ecclesiastical office of tutal bean has been revived in eighteen English dioceses since the year 1800 3 is recognised by the legislature in two recent statutoe, which have assigned to that office special duties; and is now revived in this diocese with the concurrence of the several archdeacons: the object being, not in any respect to supersede their use and authority, or to interfere with their rights and jurisdiction, but to assist them in some branches of their duty, extremely onerous in this extensive diocese, which contains 1038 parishes, and an increased population with increased religious wants.
